bilingual.target: 般若是一种深刻的智慧。

bilingual.source: This experience gave us a profound lesson.
bilingual.target: 这次经历给了我们一个深刻的教训。

bilingual.source: Her speech was filled with profound insights.
bilingual.target: 她的演讲充满了深刻的见解。

bilingual.source: The book had a profound impact on his thinking.
bilingual.target: 这本书对他的思维产生了深刻的影响。

bilingual.source: The philosopher is known for his profound aphorism.
bilingual.target: 这位哲学家以其深刻的警句而闻名。

bilingual.source: This piece of music gives a profound sense of beauty.
bilingual.target: 这首音乐作品给人一种深刻的美感。

bilingual.source: Music can touch the souls of people in profound ways.
bilingual.target: 音乐可以以深刻的方式触动人们的灵魂。

bilingual.source: Many people admire the poetess for her profound words.
bilingual.target: 许多人钦佩这位女诗人深刻的词句。

bilingual.source: His ruminations on life often lead to profound insights.
bilingual.target: 他对生活的沉思常常带来深刻的见解。

bilingual.source: Kieslowski is known for his profound storytelling in cinema.
bilingual.target: 基耶斯洛夫斯基以其深刻的电影叙事而闻名。

yingyinNormal.en: Me neither. But I just had a tickle in my throat. Not profound marital problems.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也睡不着，但我只是喉咙痒，不是什么深刻的婚姻问题。

yingyinNormal.en: So unfortunately, this doesn't help this woman, but it does have severe, profound if you will, implications to her family.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很不幸这没能帮到这位女性，但这对她的家人来说是很重要深刻的启示。

yingyinNormal.en: And that is when I came to a profound realization.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从那时起我就深刻地意识到这点。

yingyinNormal.en: It's profound. How could you not tell me about this before?
yingyinNormal.zh: 是很有前瞻性的东西，你怎么以前没和我说过？

yingyinNormal.en: It's been a major boost to our economy and a profound change to our auto industry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 成为了我们经济的巨大推动力量，并促进了我国汽车行业的深化改革。

yingyinNormal.en: My mother went through a profound change at the end of her life. She felt exactly as you do now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我妈妈在她去世之前发生过很大的变化。她的感觉就跟你现在一样。

yingyinNormal.en: On behalf of the Nova Corps, we'd like to express our profound gratitude for your help in saving Xandar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们想代表新星军团深深感谢各位协助拯救柴达。

yingyinNormal.en: And, when we exposed general Zod to the mineral, this happened. Profound biodegradation. Decaying Kryptonian cells.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当我们使佐德将军与该矿物接触时，发生了这样的事，深度生物降解，导致氪星人细胞衰减。

yingyinNormal.en: And the much longer and profound erosion of middle-class jobs and incomes isn't something we're going to reverse overnight.
yingyinNormal.zh: 更长时间和更深刻地对中产阶层就业岗位和收入的侵蚀，我们并不能在一夜之间改变它们。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_family.mean: adj. 巨大的；深刻的；深邃的；渊博的；见解深刻的；深长的；深度的；极度的；根深蒂固的

sense_info_list.en: (of a state, quality, or emotion) very great or intense

examination_example.sentence: In Ferreira’s opinion, preservation of plastic artifacts has <highlight>profound</highlight> historical significance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在费雷拉看来，塑料制品的保存具有深远的历史意义。

examination_example.sentence: This aversion to arguments is common, but it depends on a mistaken view of arguments that causes <highlight>profound</highlight> problems for our personal and social lives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种对争论的厌恶是常见的，但它取决于对争论的错误看法，这种观点会给我们个人和社会生活带来巨大的问题。

examination_example.sentence: Nor was there any evidence that those who self-enhanced the most were doing so to make up for <highlight>profound</highlight> insecurities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也没有任何证据表明，那些自我增强最多的人这样做是为了弥补其深深的不安全感。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person or statement) having or showing great knowledge or insight

examination_example.sentence: The insight that curiosity can drive you to do self-destructive things is a <highlight>profound</highlight> one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 好奇心会驱使你去做自我毁灭的事情，这一见解十分精辟。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: (of a state; quality; or emotion) very great or intense

examination_example.sentence: It is undergoing radical and <highlight>profound</highlight> changes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当前，中国正经历着根本而深刻的变化。

examination_example.sentence: A multi-stage life will have <highlight>profound</highlight> changes not just in how you manage your career, but also in your approach to life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 多阶段的人生不仅会对你的职业生涯产生深远的影响，也会对你的生活方式产生深远的影响。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Profound</highlight> changes in the workforce are making teams trickier to manage.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 劳动力的巨大变化使得团队管理变得更加棘手。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person or statement) having or showing great knowledge or insight
sense_info_list.zh: 知识渊博的; 深奥的
